Home Grown
Cherry Tomato Harvest!
My friend mentioned he sometimes hated seeing my posts about my garden or other fun things because he’s too depressed to get up and grow a garden or get outside at all.
My posts are obviously not meant to have that effect but he is not alone in this as im sure many of you like myself feel the same way sometimes.
Truthfully, I have weeks I can hardly get out of bed. I’m scared and confused and desperately scramble to make sense of the world around me and my own emotions or thoughts while endlessly doubting myself and trying to hold onto an image of something to work towards. I’m sure a lot of people can relate in one way or another.
During these bad times I’ve killed plants from neglect or done much worse but gardening has been a useful tool to keep me on a productive path and has given me many wonderful days. Many other hobbies have too.
If I can do it, I am very confident anyone reading this can too. Even if one can’t grow a garden, hobbies of all types can change one’s life. 
Just takes one step a day.
